                                         CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a case of murder and three attempted murder cases following a shooting in Kraaifontein. The incident was reported in Scottsdene on Thursday. The motive for the shooting is still unknown. The police's Andre Traut said: “A 25-year-old man was shot and killed in Scottsdene, Kraaifontein by unknown suspects. During the same incident, three males aged 17 were shot and wounded and admitted to hospital. The circumstances are being investigated and no one has been arrested yet.”